Hardware running the coherent NULL descriptor test reports completion
through the dHub semaphore's consumer query and full condition. After the
completion is popped, the consumer count correctly returns to zero but the
producer query reports count one.

The next descriptor currently rejects that asymmetric but empty state. Use
the consumer count already polled by berlin2cd_wait_semaphore() as the
authoritative empty test. Retain both query values in failure diagnostics.

This changes only transport bookkeeping. It does not submit an additional
descriptor or access NAND media.

---
 drivers/mtd/nand/raw/marvell_nand.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/mtd/nand/raw/marvell_nand.c b/drivers/mtd/nand/raw/marvell_nand.c
index dc50b03..6a22b4f 100644
